50:23.814 --> 50:25.023
- He didn't...
- VIAGO: Nick!

50:25.649 --> 50:26.983
I will tear out your tongue

50:27.067 --> 50:28.753
- and shove it down your ass!
- NICK: Deacon...

50:28.777 --> 50:29.778
VIAGO: Guys...

50:29.861 --> 50:31.154
(DEACON SNARLING)

50:31.238 --> 50:32.572
NICK: Fucking hell!

50:34.074 --> 50:35.492
DEACON: I'm going to kill you!

50:39.830 --> 50:41.289
(DEACON GRUNTING)

50:42.749 --> 50:44.292
Tear out your tongue!

50:46.878 --> 50:48.755
DEACON: You kill Petyr
with your big mouth!

50:49.423 --> 50:50.590
NICK: It was a mistake!

50:50.674 --> 50:51.800
Get up. Take a breath.

50:52.342 --> 50:54.428
DEACON: Get up
and stand on this ceiling like a man.

50:54.678 --> 50:56.680
(GRUNTING)

51:00.183 --> 51:01.184
- (SNARLING)
- (HISSING)

51:01.268 --> 51:03.079
We can talk about this, okay?
We can talk about it.

51:03.103 --> 51:04.271
DEACON: I'll kill you!

51:04.354 --> 51:05.439
I'm already dead!

51:06.440 --> 51:07.524
NICK: Stu, stay back.

51:08.859 --> 51:10.610
(GROWLING)

51:10.736 --> 51:12.320
- (KNOCKING)
- (SHUSHING)

51:12.404 --> 51:13.798
VIAGO: There's someone at the door.

51:13.822 --> 51:15.365
I'll go. I'll go.

51:23.123 --> 51:24.624
Oh, shit.

51:26.126 --> 51:27.126
Yeah, good evening, sir.

51:27.169 --> 51:28.170
Hello, Police.

51:28.253 --> 51:30.630
Hi, I'm Constable O'Leary.
This is Constable Minogue.

51:30.714 --> 51:31.941
We're just responding to reports

51:31.965 --> 51:33.675
of a possible forced entry,

51:33.759 --> 51:36.136
and also
a rather large amount of shrieking.

51:36.219 --> 51:37.447
Just wondering
if maybe we could come in,

51:37.471 --> 51:39.055
just have a wee look around.

51:39.139 --> 51:40.223
Okay.

51:40.515 --> 51:42.809
What's with the... Hello.
What's with the, um, camera?

51:42.893 --> 51:45.413
Yeah, obviously we're just here
'cause there was a phone call from

51:45.437 --> 51:47.731
a member of the public
about a bit of a disturbance.

51:47.814 --> 51:49.858
Um... Some loud noises,

51:49.941 --> 51:51.781
- possibly a forced entry, wasn't there?
- Hmm.

51:51.818 --> 51:53.487
And also maybe
a bit of smoke coming out.

51:53.570 --> 51:55.006
So we're just checking over the scene,

51:55.030 --> 51:58.200
making sure everything's above board,
so to speak,

51:58.283 --> 52:00.443
and making sure no one's in danger,
that kind of thing.

52:00.494 --> 52:01.929
We might go up
and have a wee look up there,

52:01.953 --> 52:03.580
if that's all right with you.

52:03.789 --> 52:07.250
- Just part of the job. Yep.
- Come on, mate, you lead the way.

52:07.334 --> 52:08.334
Okay.

52:08.376 --> 52:10.337
- Smells a bit weird in here, too, mate.
- Yeah.

52:10.420 --> 52:11.963
What do you call that?

52:13.673 --> 52:15.217
Barbecue.

52:18.178 --> 52:21.765
You will not notice anything
out of the ordinary.

52:22.224 --> 52:23.683
No, we certainly hope not.

52:23.767 --> 52:25.560
Let's just keep going.

52:25.644 --> 52:26.829
POLICEWOMAN: Yeah, hi there, guys.
STU: Hello.

52:26.853 --> 52:27.896
- How are you?
- Good.

52:27.979 --> 52:29.499
POLICEMAN: Hey, fellas.
VLADISLAV: Hello.

52:29.523 --> 52:31.918
POLICEWOMAN: Is this the room we've
heard all the shouting coming from?

52:31.942 --> 52:33.151
DEACON: That was me.

52:33.235 --> 52:35.087
POLICEWOMAN: Yeah, okay.
We've had a couple of reports, okay?

52:35.111 --> 52:37.548
There's a couple of people not that
happy about the level of noise here.

52:37.572 --> 52:39.217
- Okay. The neighbors?
- POLICEMAN: You can't keep screaming

52:39.241 --> 52:40.301
when there's this many
people around, mate.

52:40.325 --> 52:41.719
You've got neighbors on either side.

52:41.743 --> 52:42.911
(WHISPERING) Really nervous.

52:42.994 --> 52:44.788
I've hypnotized those cops.

52:44.871 --> 52:46.248
I'm not a great hypnotizer,

52:46.331 --> 52:48.250
so it could wear off any second.

52:48.333 --> 52:50.961
I really hope that those guys
don't kill those police

52:51.044 --> 52:53.088
because it will mean
more police will come,

52:53.171 --> 52:54.631
possibly even Christians,

52:54.714 --> 52:57.300
which is totally the last thing
we need in this house.

52:57.384 --> 52:58.844
I can see you're having a good time.

52:58.927 --> 53:01.555
End of the day,
we've got to keep the peace, okay?

53:01.638 --> 53:03.139
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

53:03.890 --> 53:05.183
See what I'm seeing?

53:05.267 --> 53:06.627
POLICEWOMAN: What's that, Minogue?

53:07.602 --> 53:08.728
You're joking.

53:10.146 --> 53:11.565
Not a smoke alarm in sight.

53:11.648 --> 53:13.316
POLICEMAN: No smoke detectors, mate.

53:13.400 --> 53:15.819
Rule number one, smoke detectors.

53:15.902 --> 53:17.112
Okay.

53:17.195 --> 53:19.823
Rule number two,
maybe not so many barbecues inside.

53:19.906 --> 53:21.386
- Sort it out, fellas.
- DEACON: Okay.

53:21.741 --> 53:23.928
POLICEMAN: Barbecue smells
really strong down here, doesn't it?

53:23.952 --> 53:25.012
- What kind of marinade...
- Yeah.

53:25.036 --> 53:26.097
What kind of marinade did you use?

53:26.121 --> 53:27.247
Who's this guy?

53:27.539 --> 53:31.167
Um... That's a friend
who came to our party.

53:31.251 --> 53:32.586
Mate, are you all right?

53:32.669 --> 53:34.063
- He's drunk.
- That's what I thought.

53:34.087 --> 53:35.338
- Drunk guy.
- Yeah.

53:35.422 --> 53:37.716
Look, you can't
just leave him down here like that, okay?

53:37.799 --> 53:39.259
This guy's not having a good time.

53:39.342 --> 53:41.094
He's gonna feel
terrible tomorrow morning.

53:41.177 --> 53:42.971
Well, his soul is in hell, so don't worry.

53:43.054 --> 53:44.240
Well, I don't know where his soul is,

53:44.264 --> 53:45.700
but all I am saying is,
where is his blanket?

53:45.724 --> 53:47.159
Okay, just check on him in the morning.

53:47.183 --> 53:48.578
There's a big slab of concrete on him.

53:48.602 --> 53:49.704
VIAGO: Yeah.
POLICEMAN: You could move that.

53:49.728 --> 53:50.830
That's definitely not
gonna be comfortable.

53:50.854 --> 53:53.082
- See anything else in here, Minogue?
- No, I've seen enough.

53:53.106 --> 53:54.983
- Okay.
- Hang on a minute.

53:55.066 --> 53:56.151
What have we got here?

53:57.944 --> 53:59.130
POLICEWOMAN: What is that?
VIAGO: This?

53:59.154 --> 54:00.155
- This?
- Oh, this?

54:00.238 --> 54:01.948
You can see it as clearly as I can.

54:02.032 --> 54:04.618
Adhesive, mate. That's a flammable.

54:04.701 --> 54:06.453
Then you've got a lamp on top of that,

54:06.536 --> 54:08.204
directly underneath a power source.

54:08.288 --> 54:09.414
That is quite bad, guys.

54:09.497 --> 54:10.808
- It's very bad.
- It's a very bad combination.

54:10.832 --> 54:12.268
And no smoke detectors again,
are there?

54:12.292 --> 54:14.377
- No.
- Yes, there are.

54:14.461 --> 54:16.463
Yes, there are.
I see them, yeah. That's good.

54:16.546 --> 54:17.815
- Lots to think about, guys.
- Okay.

54:17.839 --> 54:18.983
Yeah, lots to think about there, guys.

54:19.007 --> 54:20.359
- Well, shall we carry on?
- Next flat meeting. <i>Ja?</i>

54:20.383 --> 54:21.861
Yeah, good thinking. That's the thing.

54:21.885 --> 54:23.279
Just have a bit of dialogue about it.

54:23.303 --> 54:24.471
VIAGO: Okay.

54:24.554 --> 54:26.056
They've got a really good point.

54:26.139 --> 54:27.182
Wait. Let's kill them.

54:27.307 --> 54:28.308
No.

54:28.391 --> 54:30.727
Well, let's just see
what other safety points they have,

54:30.810 --> 54:32.812
and then maybe we'll kill them.

54:41.613 --> 54:46.493
I call into session
this trial of Nick of Wellington.

54:51.623 --> 54:53.333
VLADISLAV: Read the charges.

54:53.792 --> 54:55.669
"Problems we have with Nick.

54:56.670 --> 54:58.088
"Number One."

54:58.171 --> 55:00.090
You brought a human into our house,

55:00.173 --> 55:01.925
which is a big no-no
in the vampire world.

55:02.008 --> 55:03.259
Stu is okay, though?

55:03.343 --> 55:04.594
Yeah. Stu is fine,

55:04.678 --> 55:07.138
so I guess we'll just cross that one out.

55:07.639 --> 55:08.640
Uh...

55:12.102 --> 55:13.788
VIAGO: Thank you, Stu.
VLADISLAV: Thank you, Stu.

55:13.812 --> 55:16.356
VIAGO: So, the new Number One.

55:16.439 --> 55:19.150
"Nick's been
telling people he's a vampire.

55:19.234 --> 55:21.111
"That, in turn, resulted

55:21.194 --> 55:25.532
"in an unwanted visit
from a vampire hunter.

55:25.615 --> 55:27.283
"Crime Number Two."

55:27.367 --> 55:29.285
This is quite a biggie, Nick.

55:29.369 --> 55:31.955
The Vampire Hunter who killed Petyr.

55:33.081 --> 55:34.708
That actually should've...

55:34.791 --> 55:36.292
That should've been Crime Number One,

55:36.376 --> 55:38.378
but we wanted to build up to that.

55:38.461 --> 55:39.629
Number Three,

55:39.713 --> 55:41.339
Deacon doesn't like that you wear

55:41.423 --> 55:43.216
the same jacket as him,

55:43.299 --> 55:46.678
and he would like you
to find your own original style.

55:47.679 --> 55:52.517
For these crimes of which,
we, the Vampire Council, find you guilty,

55:52.934 --> 55:56.730
you shall be banished
from our flat indefinitely.

55:56.896 --> 55:58.815
- Indefinitely.
- Indefinitely.

55:58.898 --> 55:59.898
So I can come back?

55:59.941 --> 56:03.278
No, no.
"Indefinitely" means there is no end.

56:03.361 --> 56:04.380
- I thought it was like...
- I just think it...

56:04.404 --> 56:06.084
VIAGO: No,
"indefinite" means that it's not

56:06.114 --> 56:07.657
a definite thing, it can be changed.

56:07.741 --> 56:08.801
- Does it, though?
- Yes, but it's long.

56:08.825 --> 56:10.469
It could be tomorrow,
it could be six months.

56:10.493 --> 56:12.096
- No, it is not tomorrow.
- No, it won't be tomorrow.

56:12.120 --> 56:14.056
- Forget about it. You're banished.
- It's at least six months.

56:14.080 --> 56:15.331
- You're banished.
- That's it.

56:15.415 --> 56:16.809
VLADISLAV: But, Stu,
you can visit if you like.

56:16.833 --> 56:18.126
Thank you.

56:18.793 --> 56:22.422
DEACON: For your crimes,
you will be made to suffer

56:22.714 --> 56:25.050
the Procession of Shame.

56:25.133 --> 56:28.261
I asked them, Nick.
I asked them not to pass that sentence.

56:28.344 --> 56:30.513
We should do this immediately,
in my opinion.

56:30.597 --> 56:31.598
You didn't ask.

56:32.057 --> 56:34.434
You didn't ask. You were saying yes.

56:37.896 --> 56:39.707
- I didn't. Well, I...
- Well, this is what's going to happen.

56:39.731 --> 56:41.399
I still think it's quite extreme.

56:42.442 --> 56:45.862
Let us do the Procession of Shame now.

56:47.781 --> 56:48.799
VLADISLAV: Shame.
DEACON: Shame.

56:48.823 --> 56:50.033
VIAGO: Shame. Shame. Shame.

56:50.116 --> 56:51.260
VLADISLAV: Shame. Shame. Shame.

56:51.284 --> 56:52.285
DEACON: Shame!

56:52.368 --> 56:53.679
VIAGO: Bad vampire!
DEACON: Shame.

56:53.703 --> 56:54.704
VLADISLAV: Shame.

56:56.247 --> 56:57.499
Should we go, Stu?

57:03.171 --> 57:04.251
VIAGO: (WHISPERS) Bye, Stu.

57:07.801 --> 57:09.385
(GATE CREAKING)

57:20.897 --> 57:22.017
VLADISLAV: That was a shame.

57:33.201 --> 57:34.786
(SIGHING)

57:46.256 --> 57:48.758
DEACON: <i>So today
we have an invitation</i>

57:49.843 --> 57:52.595
<i>to the big event of the year.</i>

57:52.679 --> 57:54.139
VIAGO: Breaking it open.

57:54.973 --> 57:56.432
DEACON: They have burned the edges.

57:56.516 --> 57:57.993
VIAGO: Like a treasure map
or something.

57:58.017 --> 57:59.857
VLADISLAV: It looks very authentic,
doesn't it?

58:00.478 --> 58:02.021
"Dearly departed..."

58:02.355 --> 58:03.606
That's us.

58:04.232 --> 58:06.484
"The Wellington Vampire Association

58:06.568 --> 58:09.612
"in conjunction with
the Lower Hutt Vampire Witch Club

58:09.696 --> 58:12.282
"and the Karori Zombie Society

58:12.699 --> 58:15.869
"invites you to attend
The Unholy Masquerade

58:16.327 --> 58:19.455
"on the night of the 6th of June,

58:19.706 --> 58:22.709
"starting at 6:00 p.m."

58:23.835 --> 58:24.835
666.

58:24.878 --> 58:25.962
Oh, yeah.

58:26.045 --> 58:27.731
VLADISLAV:
<i>The Unholy Masquerade, of course,</i>

58:27.755 --> 58:30.592
is great time
for the undead community of Wellington.

58:30.675 --> 58:32.218
There's zombies there,

58:32.302 --> 58:36.848
<i>vampires, banshees,
all having a dance together.</i>

58:36.931 --> 58:38.850
<i>It's always a big deal for me.</i>

58:38.933 --> 58:39.934
Love it.

58:40.018 --> 58:42.395
One year I went
to The Unholy Masquerade

58:42.478 --> 58:44.564
dressed as Whoopi Goldberg

58:44.647 --> 58:50.069
from <i>Sister Act 1</i>
and <i>Sister Act 2: Back in the Habit.</i>

58:50.153 --> 58:53.531
It didn't go down so well
because she was a nun.

58:54.324 --> 58:57.285
We vampires don't like nuns.

58:57.368 --> 59:00.038
VLADISLAV: <i>Of course the big
deal of The Unholy Masquerade is,</i>

59:00.121 --> 59:02.373
<i>every year they announce
a Guest of Honor.</i>

59:04.500 --> 59:06.961
And I don't know
if I should be saying this,

59:07.670 --> 59:09.422
but I heard a little rumor

59:09.505 --> 59:12.425
that the Guest of Honor this year

59:13.426 --> 59:14.802
might be me.

59:15.970 --> 59:17.513
DEACON: The location...

59:17.597 --> 59:18.699
VLADISLAV: Oh, where?
Yeah, where is it?

59:18.723 --> 59:19.723
Oh, the location.

59:19.766 --> 59:21.184
The Cathedral of Despair.

59:21.267 --> 59:23.603
And the Guest of Honor will be...

59:27.106 --> 59:29.108
Who is it? Show me.

59:35.907 --> 59:36.908
Mmm.

59:38.034 --> 59:40.870
VLADISLAV: (SIGHING) Okay. Okay.

59:41.663 --> 59:43.414
Okay. Okay, that's fine. That's fine.

59:43.498 --> 59:44.791
Okay?

59:45.959 --> 59:47.001
(VLADISLAV SHOUTING)

59:47.085 --> 59:48.795
I can't believe it!

59:48.878 --> 59:51.130
(CRASHING)

59:51.256 --> 59:54.092
Vladislav has

59:54.175 --> 59:57.387
just had a reaction to the information

59:57.470 --> 01:00:00.390
that the Guest of Honor will be, um...

01:00:00.473 --> 01:00:01.641
The Beast.

01:00:05.144 --> 01:00:09.315
The darkest part of my mind
is reserved for The Beast.

01:00:09.399 --> 01:00:11.210
We could tell you a thing or two
about The Beast.

01:00:11.234 --> 01:00:13.987
You should pray
that you never have to see The Beast.

01:00:14.070 --> 01:00:15.863
This one is called The Beast.

01:00:15.947 --> 01:00:19.033
And I said,
"Get your hands off my balls, Beast!"

01:00:19.117 --> 01:00:20.827
He may have told you some stories

01:00:20.910 --> 01:00:23.413
about his great battle with The Beast.

01:00:23.496 --> 01:00:25.915
Yeah. "Oh, I fought The Beast on a cliff.

01:00:25.999 --> 01:00:28.418
"Oh, I fought The Beast in a swamp.

01:00:29.002 --> 01:00:30.586
"And then one time I fought The Beast

01:00:30.670 --> 01:00:32.714
"in the toilets of a nightclub."

01:00:33.172 --> 01:00:34.465
Difficult battle.

01:00:34.549 --> 01:00:37.593
I hope you never see The Beast.

01:00:38.428 --> 01:00:40.263
The Beast.

01:00:49.355 --> 01:00:52.608
You can't go to the ball as Blade.
He's a vampire hunter.

01:00:52.692 --> 01:00:55.111
VIAGO: Yeah, but vampires
love Wesley Snipes, so it's...

01:00:55.194 --> 01:00:56.529
No, it's inappropriate.

01:00:56.612 --> 01:00:58.531
Okay, Vlad, the green jodhpurs

01:00:58.614 --> 01:01:01.034
or the black leather with the dragon belt?

01:01:01.117 --> 01:01:02.177
I'm having a mild crisis here.

01:01:02.201 --> 01:01:03.262
Just wear the pants you're going to wear.

01:01:03.286 --> 01:01:04.346
Which pants do you want to wear?

01:01:04.370 --> 01:01:06.140
Just look at the pants, Vlad.
Turn around and look at them.

01:01:06.164 --> 01:01:07.373
They're just pants!

01:01:07.457 --> 01:01:09.125
- Shit, man!
- Holy shit!

01:01:09.709 --> 01:01:11.044
VIAGO: Oh, you look terrible.

01:01:11.127 --> 01:01:12.170
The black pants.

01:01:12.587 --> 01:01:14.088
Thank you. Get dressed.

01:01:14.172 --> 01:01:16.257
I don't know if I feel up to it, really.

01:01:16.341 --> 01:01:17.359
VIAGO: You don't look that great,

01:01:17.383 --> 01:01:18.885
but if you eat someone on the way

01:01:18.968 --> 01:01:20.487
- and rejuvenate a little bit...
- I'm fine. I just...

01:01:20.511 --> 01:01:22.231
You could probably
wear a mask or something.

01:01:22.305 --> 01:01:25.641
Just leave me to do
my dark bidding on the Internet.

01:01:25.725 --> 01:01:27.268
What are you bidding on?

01:01:27.352 --> 01:01:29.437
I'm bidding on a table.

01:01:29.520 --> 01:01:31.356
- Are you coming or not?
- Not.

01:01:31.439 --> 01:01:33.691
VIAGO: I'm gonna go change.
We're leaving in 10 minutes.

01:01:33.775 --> 01:01:34.776
(SIGHS)

01:01:34.859 --> 01:01:35.860
